    "body": "Thanks for adding this extra info, @zcbenz! It's really helpful.\n\nI made a few changes as well, but nothing that challenges the existing rules of the styleguide.\n\nOne minor thing: \n\n> All words in the page's title must be capitalized.\n\nTitlecasing is a highly subjective thing, but in general articles and conjunctions like \"of\" and \"and\" are not capitalized in American English. Some examples from the existing docs:\n- Technical Differences Between Electron and NW.js (formerly node-webkit)\n- Debugging on Windows\n- Setting Up Symbol Server in Debugger\n"
