    "updated_at": "2016-06-25T06:38:24Z",
    "body": "> don't know how to describe this style of titling\n\nIt's colloquially known as \"title case\", but there is no strict definition. The closest thing to a standard is [AP Style](https://www.bkacontent.com/how-to-correctly-use-apa-style-title-case/). I couldn't find a node module that implements AP-style title casing, so I wrote one: https://github.com/zeke/ap-style-title-case#readme\n"
